theorem closure_diff_subset_closure_left_diff_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A \ interior B) ⊆ closure A \ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, `x` lies in `closure A` because `A \ interior B ⊆ A`.
  have hxClA : x ∈ closure A :=
    (closure_mono (Set.diff_subset : A \ interior B ⊆ A)) hx
  -- Next, show that `x ∉ interior B`.
  have hxNotIntB : x ∉ interior B := by
    intro hxIntB
    -- Since `interior B` is open and contains `x`, membership of `x` in the
    -- closure of `A \ interior B` forces their intersection to be non‐empty.
    have hNon :
        ((interior B) ∩ (A \ interior B)).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hx (interior B) isOpen_interior hxIntB
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, hyIntB, hyDiff⟩
    -- But `y ∈ A \ interior B` implies `y ∉ interior B`, a contradiction.
    exact hyDiff.2 hyIntB
  exact And.intro hxClA hxNotIntB

theorem closure_nonempty_iff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    (closure A).Nonempty ↔ A.Nonempty := by
  constructor
  · intro hCl
    by_contra hA
    have hAeq : A = (∅ : Set X) :=
      Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty.mp hA
    simpa [hAeq, closure_empty] using hCl
  · intro hA
    rcases hA with ⟨x, hxA⟩
    exact ⟨x, (subset_closure : A ⊆ closure A) hxA⟩
